.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# Python bytecode cache (e.g. from running amplicon_annotate/merge_report.py)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# ── Committed example & reference data (all under examples/) ─────────────────────────
# The globals above ignore real data (*.fastq.gz, *.bam, output/, runs/, AND the bare
# `amplicon/` pipeline-output dir-name, etc.). These negations re-include ONLY the shipped
# fixtures under examples/. Order matters (last match wins) and DIRECTORIES must be
# re-included BEFORE files: `!examples/**/` defeats the bare `output/` and `amplicon/`
# dir-ignores so git descends into examples/amplicon and the wf-amplicon_*/output and
# reference_run_canu/output trees; `!examples/**` then defeats *.fastq.gz / *.bam / *.fastq.
!examples/
!examples/**/
!examples/**

# ── LOCAL-ONLY amplicon (Mode B testing) — NEVER commit ──────────────────────────────
# barcode39_example/'s insert exposes unpublished research. Re-ignored AFTER the allowlist
# above (last match wins) so an accidental `git add` is blocked. BOTH lines are required:
# the dir line blocks adding the folder; the `/**` line re-ignores the files that the
# aggressive `!examples/**` above would otherwise re-include. Keep it on disk for local
# SPLIT/Mode-B runs; do NOT commit.
examples/amplicon/barcode39_example/
examples/amplicon/barcode39_example/**
